{
  "answer": "The matlaʿ (opening couplet) of this ghazal by Mirza Ghalib is:\n\n> حیراں ہوں دل کو روؤں کہ پیٹوں جگر کو میں  \n> مقدور ہو تو ساتھ رکھوں نوحہ_گر کو میں[^1]\n\n> Hairaan hoon dil ko roun ke peetun jigar ko main  \n> Maqdoor ho to saath rakhun nauha-gar ko main[^2]\n\nThe speaker faces the dilemma of whether to cry over (roun) his heart (dil, seat of emotion) or beat/tear (peetun) his liver (jigar, seat of profound passion or suffering).[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 65 (\"Hairaan hoon dil ko roun ke peetun jigar ko main\"), [p-cfda65](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/65-hairaan-hoon-dil-ko-roun-ke-peetun-jigar-ko-main/original/#p-cfda65).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 65 (\"Hairaan hoon dil ko roun ke peetun jigar ko main\"), transliteration, [p-509dee](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/65-hairaan-hoon-dil-ko-roun-ke-peetun-jigar-ko-main/transliteration/#p-509dee).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 65 (\"Hairaan hoon dil ko roun ke peetun jigar ko main\"), [p-a750b7](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/65-hairaan-hoon-dil-ko-roun-ke-peetun-jigar-ko-main/translation/#p-a750b7).",
